    "created_at": "2021-07-14T22:44:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2021-07-14T22:48:40Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "What I see in TransactionReplacementByPriceRule is that we replace if the *effective price* of the transaction is above a threshold percentage of the existing transaction, not the effective priorityFee.\r\n\r\nIt seems to me the correct behavior here is subjective.\r\n* if the miner were 100% altruistic, they would:\r\n  * always want to replace a transaction with one with a higher effective price (this is the current implementation)\r\n\r\n* if the miner were 100% selfish, they would:\r\n  * always want to replace a transaction with one with a higher effective priority fee\r\n  * only want to replace with a similar effective priority fee if the effective price is higher (since it has a higher likelihood of executing)\r\n  * never replace an existing transaction with one with a lower effective priority fee\r\n\r\nThat last point is not 100% certain.  A selfish miner might want to replace a transaction with one with a lower effective priority fee IF there was a better chance it would execute and net some revenue versus no revenue.\r\n",
